BUDDING boxing promotions company, Thobela Ledwaba Bergman  (TLB) Boxing Promotions, has promised to help elevate the career of talented but unlucky Xolisani “Nomeva” Ndongeni to the next level.Despite the boxing prowess the unbeaten Eastern Cape born fighter possesses his boxing career has stagnated due to misfortune and inactivity. If TLB’s vow is anything to go by, there may finally be a light at the end of the tunnel for 27-year-old Ndongeni.The lanky warrior is scheduled to take on the Namibian, Abraham Ndaendopa, for the World Boxing Federation world lightweight title at Times Square Sun in Menlyn, Tshwane, on 6 April. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsvoXkbszUpRXyX-4xTGQlPpLMlxeJJjGxCrk4GgO3FN137fuqAIm_RBuyfqQrFqDvuWl7DloAhkQHTEpFa4fUEOqQl0zRdy8Oc00M6Xs9s_sl5_HIkFTsetr4BWQDgJLCahG13SjjXbYSYUz1iiu9m7n61UqbC1Dv1ufKswOwznTJ1BEtxu-8DuW9UgcuDyWOo91lA5PZPq3Ws7z8aVEm_O_Vuqbc4ESjc3CDSQrIXYDPUDjRpQQiWkHKyDDJBa8VeXWcvNy7xfufVhyCso\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzH1tk-rqEjnCEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
